{{Wireless embedded system |brand=TP-LINK |model=TD-W8951ND |revision=V3 |series=TD-W8951ND |fcc_date=12/21/2010 |manuf_country=China |is_manuf=Yes |type=wireless router,dsl modem |fcc_id=TE7TDW8951NDV3 |pwr_v=9 |pwr_amp=0.85 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=TrendChip |cpu1_model=TC3162U |fla1=2 MiB |fla1_brand=Eon |fla1_model=F16-100HIP |ram1=16 MiB |ram1_brand=ESMT |ram1_model=M12L128168A-6T |wi1_chip1_brand=Ralink |wi1_chip1_model=RT3390 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=RP-SMA |wi1_txchains=1 |wi1_rxchains=1 |wi1_sstreams=1 |eth_cpu=true |sw_brand=TrendChip |sw_model=TC2205F |lan_speed=100M |lan_ports=4 |addl_chips=DSL (ADSL2+) AFE;TrendChip;TC3086;;1; |flags=ADSL2+ |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ip=192.168.1.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin |default_ch= }} {{TagLine|150Mbps Wireless N ADSL2+ Modem Router}} :[http://www.tp-link.com/en/products/details/?model=TD-W8951ND Product page]
"10091328951-3.0" and "Rev:1.0sp1" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
Per [[User:Cuonic]], this device is using the following... *ADSL SoC: [http://www.mediatek.com/_en/01_products/04_pro.php?sn=1020 '''TrendChip''' TC3162U] **ADSL AFE: [http://www.mediatek.com/_en/01_products/04_pro.php?sn=1021 '''TrendChip''' TC3086] *RAM: '''ESMT''' M12L128168A-6T ([http://www.esmt.com.tw/DB/manager/upload/M12L128168A.pdf Datasheet]) *Wi-Fi: RT3398L (presumably in error? RT3390 would seem to be the only [commonly known] 1T1R 339x) *Switch: [[http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/trendchip-introduces-the-first-energy-saving-switch-chip-designed-specifically-for-broadband-access-platforms-94240724.html '''TrendChip''' TC2205F]
.. and per the images, the serial Flash used would appear to be a '''Eon''' F16-100HIP (2 MB).
